'''Ali Mufuruki''' is a [[Tanzanian]] businessman, author, founder and board member of several organisations. He is the founder of Infotech Investment Group, founding chairman of CEO Roundtable of Tanzania and Africa Leadership Initiative (ALI) East Africa, board chairman of [[Vodacom Tanzania]] and Wananchi Group Holdings, trustee of the [[Mandela Institute for Development Studies]] (MINDS) and co-author of the book ''Tanzania's Industrialisation Journey, 2016-2056''.<ref name = "ventures">{{cite news |last=Iweala |first=Uzodinma |date=23 November 2012 |title=Africa’s Secret Millionaires: The 5 Richest Tanzanians You’ve Never Heard Of |url=http://www.ventures-africa.com/2012/11/africas-secret-millionaires-the-5-richest-tanzanians-youve-never-heard-of/ |newspaper= |location= |publisher=ventures-africa.com |accessdate= 3 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Tungaraza |first=Elizabeth |date=9 February 2014 |title=Doting father, husband and businessman |url=http://www.thecitizen.co.tz/oped/Doting-father--husband-and-businessman/-/1840568/2198682/-/item/0/-/rmn3b/-/index.html |newspaper= [[The Citizen (Tanzania)]] |location= |publisher= |accessdate= 3 September 2014}}</ref><ref name = "industrialisation">{{cite news |last=Willem te Velde |first=Dirk |date=9 October 2017 |title=Fostering a debate around practical industrialisation models in Tanzania |url=https://set.odi.org/fostering-debate-industrialisation-models-tanzania/ |newspaper= |location= |publisher=set.odi.org |accessdate= 30 July 2018}}</ref><ref name = "global philanthropy">{{cite news |last=|first=|date=1 January 2017 |title=Ali Mufuruki |url=https://philanthropyforum.org/people/ali-a-mufuruki/ |newspaper= |location= |publisher=philanthropyforum.org |accessdate= 30 July 2018}}</ref>
