'''Anette Gleichmann''', née '''Skaugen''' (born 1964) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] investor and publisher.
She is a part of a large shipping family, as a daughter of [[Brynjulf Skaugen, Sr.|Brynjulf Skaugen, Sr]]. She changed her surname after marrying [[Sweden|Swedish]] Gabi Gleichmann.
In 2010 she and her husband started the publishing house Agora Publishing, in order to publish translations of [[world literature]] hitherto untranslated to [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]].<ref>{{cite news|url=|title=Tetter hull i norske bokhyller|last=Hallheim|first=Rune|date=17 November 2010|work=Aftenposten|page=|language=Norwegian|accessdate=}}</ref>
