{{Expand Polish|Karol Łazarz Henckel von Donnersmarck|date=April 2012}} '''Karol Łazarz Henckel von Donnersmarck''' (5 March 1772 – 12 July 1864) was a [[Germany|German]] businessman founding amongst others the mines in [[Katowice]] which now house the [[Silesian Museum]].
