A '''designated activity company''' ([[Irish language|Irish]]: '''Cuideachta Ghníomhaíochta Ainmnithe''') or '''DAC''' is a form of company in [[Ireland]] created by the [[Companies Act 2014]]. Notable DACs include [[Ryanair]] and [[Ulster Bank]].


