{{Infobox officeholder |name = Oliver Janich |image = |imagesize = |birth_place = [[Munich]], [[Germany]] |nationality = {{flag|Germany}} |party = [[Party of Reason]] (2009-present) |alma_mater = |occupation = |profession = [[journalist]], [[author]] |signature = |website = {{de icon}} [http://www.oliverjanich.de/ Personal website] }} '''Oliver Janich''' is a German journalist and author as well as a politician, founder and former president of the [[Party of Reason|Partei der Vernunft]] (Party of Reason).<ref>[http://www.fair-news.de/pressemitteilung-18932.html Partei der Vernunft gegründet] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140529052608/http://www.fair-news.de/pressemitteilung-18932.html |date=2014-05-29 }} {{de-icon}}, 4 June 2009.</ref>
== Biography == Janich completed the apprenticeship as a bank clerk and studied [[business economics]]. He was employed at the business mags [[Euro (journal)|Euro am Sonntag]] and [[Focus (German magazine)|Focus Money]], and afterwards he wrote as a freelance journalist for the [[Financial Times Deutschland]], [[Euro (journal)|Euro]], the [[Süddeutsche Zeitung]] and at last for [[Kopp Verlag|Kopp Online]]. He lives in Munich. In 2013 he left the Party of Reason.
== Works == * Money-Management. Rationalität und Anwendung des Fixed-fractional-Ansatzes. TM-Börsenverlag, Rosenheim 1996, {{ISBN|3-930851-10-5}} * Das Kapitalismus-Komplott. Die geheimen Zirkel der Macht und ihre Methoden. FinanzBuch-Verlag, München 2010, {{ISBN|978-3-89879-577-7}} * Die Vereinigten Staaten von Europa. Geheimdokumente enthüllen: Die dunklen Pläne der Elite. FinanzBuch-Verlag, München 2013, {{ISBN|978-3-89879-820-4}}
